Serves: 8Polenta cake:240g (2 cups) polenta1.75 litres (7 cups) water125ml ( cup) fresh corn kernels (trimmed from the cob)10ml (2 tsp) saltFreshly ground black pepper, to taste2 cloves garlic, chopped2 sprigs fresh thyme, leaves only30ml (2 tbsp) olive oilTopping:300g cherry tomatoes, halved1 red onion, quartered and thinly sliced1 clove garlic, chopped15ml (1 tbsp) olive oil15ml (1 tbsp) chopped fresh marjoram or oregano leaves6 olives, pitted and sliced5ml (1 tsp) sesame seedsSalt and pepper to tasteFeel your food with conscious eatingBasil cashew drizzle:250ml (1 cup) extra virgin olive oil60ml (4 tbsp) toasted cashew nuts2.5ml ( tsp) salt2.5ml ( tsp) freshly ground black pepper1 small garlic clove, chopped30ml (2 tbsp) fresh lemon juice30g (a large bunch) fresh basilMethod:1) For the cake, whisk the polenta with 3 cups of the water to form a paste. 2) Heat the remaining 1 litre (4 cups) water in a large saucepan with the remaining polenta cake ingredients and bring to the boil.3) Add the polenta paste slowly, mixing well until smooth and combined. Reduce heat, cover and simmer gently for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.4) Grease a 23cm springform pan.5) Combine all the topping ingredients in a bowl and mix lightly.6) Pour the cooked polenta evenly into the greased pan and smooth out.7) Arrange the topping over the polenta, pressing gently to secure. Allow to stand for at least 1 hour to set.8) Heat oven to 220 C and bake the cake on the middle rack until the tomatoes begin to split and blacken, about 15 minutes.9) For the Basil cashew drizzle, place all the ingredients except the basil in a food processor and blend until smooth.10) Add the basil and blend until smooth.11) Seal in a sterilised jar and refrigerate until ready to use.12) Remove polenta cake from oven and serve hot or cold, cut into wedges and topped with the basil cashew drizzle or simply shredded fresh basil.